news.title: NHB tightens oversight on HFCs after Aviom India Housing fraud
news.para: NHB, which has been conducting periodic inspections at HFCs, has called for stricter compliance during those audits, people in the know said.

news.title: Only 5,648 homes allotted to migrant workers under ARHC scheme in 4.5 years
news.para: This is less than 7% of the 83,534 houses that were identified for the scheme when it was approved by the Cabinet.

news.title: Credai Gujarat submits memorandums to district collectors opposing proposed jantri rates
news.para: Claiming that the jantri rates proposed were not derived scientifically, the real estate developers and farmers across the state have been opposing the govt's proposal.

news.title: Bombay HC upholds tenants’ right to redevelop dilapidated Kalbadevi building
news.para: They quashed and set aside Mhada's July 8 order to the landlords to submit a redevelopment proposal and the July 10 letter of intent (LoI) permitting them to undertake the building's redevelopment.

news.title: Gurugram: All towers of Chintels Paradiso declared unsafe, set for demolition
news.para: In its latest report, Central Building Research Institute (CBRI) has found that Tower B has severe structural flaws, including widespread cracks, corroded reinforcement bars and substandard concrete, findings similar to those in the other towers.

news.title: West Bengal introduces unit area assessment for property tax reform
news.para: If a property's tax assessment continues for more than five years without reassessment, the annual value will be deemed to increase by 5 to 10% every five years as an interim measure until a new assessment list is finalised.

news.title: Noida: Lift registrations stall as residents and administration clash over guidelines
news.para: On Nov 21, a delegation from Noida Federation of Apartment Owners' Association (NOFAA) — representing over 100 societies in Noida — met the district magistrate and additional district magistrate, seeking clarity on the registration process. RWAs, however, have yet to initiate lift registrations since that meeting.

news.title: Bombay HC seeks state's response on Clan City flat buyers' plea
news.para: Justices Ajay Gadkari and Kamal Khata on Dec 6 passed the direction on a petition by Clan City Welfare Association that represents 157 flat purchasers.

news.title: Bihar RERA to auction confiscated land of defaulting builder to refund homebuyers
news.para: "The authority had confiscated the land of Agrani Homes Private Limited in Dhawalpura locality of Patna in April 2023 due to the failure of the promoter to refund the amount taken from the homebuyers after failing to complete its project," an official of the RERA told TOI on Monday.

news.title: Brookfield India REIT launches QIP to raise up to Rs 3,500 crore
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Brookfield India Real Estate Trust informed that the Issue Committee of the board of directors of Brookprop Management Services Pvt Ltd -- manager to Brookfield India REIT -- approved the opening of the QIP (qualified institutional placement) issue on Monday.

news.title: Adani Group to invest $88 billion in Rajasthan, first since US indictments
news.para: Adani Group plans to set up four new cement plants to build additional capacity of six million metric tons per annum.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh govt directs development authorities to make list of farmers eligible for compensation
news.para: Chief secretary Manoj Kumar Singh and DGP Prashant Kumar, who were in Greater Noida, held a closed-door meeting with officials from the district administration and the three development authorities.

news.title: ASK Property Fund, KREEVA & Shapoorji Pallonji to invest Rs 270 crore in housing project in Gurugram
news.para: Bhavin Jain, CIO of ASK Property Fund, said, "With significant equity from KREEVA and partnership with Shapoorji Pallonji Real Estate, this project effectively minimises risk."

news.title: Kanpur metro completes track construction up to Kanpur Central
news.para: In the coming days, the installation of the third rail on the ‘downline' to Kanpur Central will also be completed. Construction of track slabs on the Baradevi-Naubasta elevated section is progressing rapidly.

news.title: Trump Organization leases brand for two new real estate projects in Saudi Arabia
news.para: It will partner with Dar Global, a London-based luxury real estate developer that will lease the Trump brand but fully own and develop the projects in the Saudi capital, Riyadh.

news.title: Bharat Agri Fert & Realty to invest Rs 85 crore in expansion of resort in Palghar
news.para: The expansion is part of the company's strategic vision to position the resort as a venue for destination weddings and corporate events, in line with the Government of India's 'Wed in India' initiative, a company statement said.

news.title: Mysuru: Delay in relocation of Changadi village from MM Hills Sanctuary worries residents
news.para: The state govt constituted a committee headed by then Chamarajanagar deputy commissioner Charulatha Somal and the then MM Hills deputy conservator of forests (DCF) Y Edukondalu to prepare a master plan for their relocation.

news.title: Mumbai Metro 3 completes track laying for BKC-Cuffe Parade
news.para: The 12.5km long Phase I corridor (Aarey-BKC) was inaugurated on Oct 5 and opened for commuters on Oct 7. It has an average ridership of 22,000 per day.

news.title: Delhi government clarifies launch of voluntary disclosure scheme to NGT
news.para: The decision had come following a meeting involving secretary (environment), DJB CEO, and Central Groundwater Authority chairman. A public advertisement was issued in 2014, requesting details from all private and govt entities using tubewells and borewells.

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body razes flat with valuables inside during redevelopment work
news.para: The ward officer further added that since the Gawdi family earlier filed a case in the Judicial Magistrate First Class Court at Belapur over certain objections to the redevelopment issue, they alleged that such a hurried demolition of their flat was wrong and not required. This is why the NMMC stop work notice was sent.
